article.headline: N. Illinois 72, Judson (Ill.) 54
article.story: DE KALB, Ill. -- Sam Mader and Akeem Springs scored 16 points apiece and Northern Illinois won its home opener, defeating Judson of Illinois 72-54 on Sunday. Kevin Gray had 10 points and eight rebounds to lead the Huskies (1-2), who dropped road games at Nebraska-Omaha and Valparaiso. The Eagles (2-6), who play in NAIA Division II, jumped out to a 20-12 lead. NIU answered by running off 15 straight points and eventually led 39-32 at halftime. Luke Pearson and Luke Labedzki led Judson with nine points -- each of them hitting three 3-pointers. It was the first meeting between the schools.
